718391f-a.text:
Central Park: Sailboat Pool, with Fifth Avenue and 75th Street in the background. The top of the Carlyle apartment house is just visible over the roof of the apartment building adjoining the
synagogue on Fifth Avenue.
May 17, 1933.
P. L. Sperr.

718388f-a.text:
Central Park: A set of 2 views northward across the Sailboat (also hnown as the Conservatory) Lake and showing buildings lining the eastern confine of the Park; Fifth Ave. Upon the latter, they progress northward from East 75th Street which appears on the right. The Synagogue shown is at the S.E. corner of East 76th Street and the Avenue.
May 2, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.

709142f-a.text:
Fifth Ave., east side, south from and including East 75th Street. Shown on the right, is a portion of Central Park which forms the west side of Fifth Ave. at this point.
1936.
W.P.A. Photo.
Federal Writers Project.

709143f-a.text:
Fifth Ave, east side, north from and including 75th Street. The view shows Temple Beth El, completed in 1891.
About 1895.

709144f-a.text:
Fifth Avenue, east side, at 76th Street, showing Temple Beth-Hi ("House of God") at the S.E. corner. The construction of this synagogue was completed in 1891.
July 25, 1927.
